#: ../../../api/dns.rst:2
msgid "`_dns` -- DNS resolution utilities"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/dns.rst:6
msgid ""
"This module contains a few experimental utilities to interact with the DNS "
"server before performing a connection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/dns.rst:10
msgid ""
"This module is experimental and its interface could change in the future, "
"without warning or respect for the version scheme. It is provided here to "
"allow experimentation before making it more stable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/dns.rst:15
msgid ""
"This module depends on the `dnspython`_ package. The package is currently "
"not installed automatically as a Psycopg dependency and must be installed "
"manually:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/dns.rst:19
msgid "$ pip install \"dnspython >= 2.1\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/dns.rst:28
msgid "Apply SRV DNS lookup as defined in :RFC:`2782`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/dns.rst:0
msgid "Parameters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/dns.rst:30 ../../../api/dns.rst:106
msgid ""
"The input parameters, for instance as returned by `~psycopg.conninfo."
"conninfo_to_dict()`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/dns.rst:0
msgid "Returns"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/dns.rst:33
msgid "An updated list of connection parameters."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/dns.rst:35
msgid ""
"For every host defined in the ``params[\"host\"]`` list (comma-separated), "
"perform SRV lookup if the host is in the form ``_Service._Proto.Target``. If "
"lookup is successful, return a params dict with hosts and ports replaced "
"with the looked-up entries."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/dns.rst:40
msgid ""
"Raise `~psycopg.OperationalError` if no lookup is successful and no host "
"(looked up or unchanged) could be returned."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/dns.rst:43
msgid ""
"In addition to the rules defined by RFC 2782 about the host name pattern, "
"perform SRV lookup also if the the port is the string ``SRV`` (case "
"insensitive)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/dns.rst:48
msgid "This is an experimental functionality."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/dns.rst:51
msgid ""
"One possible way to use this function automatically is to subclass `~psycopg."
"Connection`, extending the `~psycopg.Connection._get_connection_params()` "
"method::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/dns.rst:55
msgid ""
"import psycopg._dns  # not imported automatically\n"
"\n"
"class SrvCognizantConnection(psycopg.Connection):\n"
"    @classmethod\n"
"    def _get_connection_params(cls, conninfo, **kwargs):\n"
"        params = super()._get_connection_params(conninfo, **kwargs)\n"
"        params = psycopg._dns.resolve_srv(params)\n"
"        return params\n"
"\n"
"# The name will be resolved to db1.example.com\n"
"cnn = SrvCognizantConnection.connect(\"host=_postgres._tcp.db.psycopg.org\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/dns.rst:71
msgid "Async equivalent of `resolve_srv()`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/connection.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.connection.Connection._get_connection_params:1
#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/connection_async.py:docstring
#: psycopg.connection_async.AsyncConnection._get_connection_params:1
msgid "Manipulate connection parameters before connecting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/dns.rst:77 ../../../api/dns.rst:93
msgid "This is an experimental method."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/dns.rst:79
msgid ""
"This method is a subclass hook allowing to manipulate the connection "
"parameters before performing the connection. Make sure to call the `!"
"super()` implementation before further manipulation of the arguments::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/dns.rst:83
msgid ""
"@classmethod\n"
"def _get_connection_params(cls, conninfo, **kwargs):\n"
"    params = super()._get_connection_params(conninfo, **kwargs)\n"
"    # do something with the params\n"
"    return params"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/dns.rst:99
msgid "Perform async DNS lookup of the hosts and return a new params dict."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/dns.rst:101
msgid ""
"The use of this function is not necessary anymore, because `psycopg."
"AsyncConnection.connect()` performs non-blocking name resolution "
"automatically."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/dns.rst:110
msgid ""
"If a ``host`` param is present but not ``hostname``, resolve the host "
"addresses dynamically."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/dns.rst:113
msgid ""
"The function may change the input ``host``, ``hostname``, ``port`` to allow "
"connecting without further DNS lookups, eventually removing hosts that are "
"not resolved, keeping the lists of hosts and ports consistent."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/dns.rst:117
msgid ""
"Raise `~psycopg.OperationalError` if connection is not possible (e.g. no "
"host resolve, inconsistent lists length)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/dns.rst:120
msgid ""
"See `the PostgreSQL docs`__ for explanation of how these params are used, "
"and how they support multiple entries."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/dns.rst:127
msgid ""
"Before psycopg 3.1, this function doesn't handle the ``/etc/hosts`` file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/dns.rst:130
msgid ""
"Starting from psycopg 3.1, a similar operation is performed automatically by "
"`!AsyncConnection._get_connection_params()`, so this function is unneeded."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/dns.rst:134
msgid ""
"In psycopg 3.0, one possible way to use this function automatically is to "
"subclass `~psycopg.AsyncConnection`, extending the `~psycopg.AsyncConnection."
"_get_connection_params()` method::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/dns.rst:138
msgid ""
"import psycopg._dns  # not imported automatically\n"
"\n"
"class AsyncDnsConnection(psycopg.AsyncConnection):\n"
"    @classmethod\n"
"    async def _get_connection_params(cls, conninfo, **kwargs):\n"
"        params = await super()._get_connection_params(conninfo, **kwargs)\n"
"        params = await psycopg._dns.resolve_hostaddr_async(params)\n"
"        return params"
msgstr ""
